<br>
- What are all the methods that can be used to 'ink' pencil work, in preparation for CG'ing?<br>
<br>
- In Manga/anime, what different styles are there?<br>
<br>
- How does manga differ from 'Marvel' or any other style of comic.<br>
<br>
- Is a wacom tablet worth its price?<br>
<br>
and finally............<br>
<br>
- Is there any books that would be bemificial to read in order to get better at drawing anime?<br>
<br>
<br>
Any answers to these questions would be great!!! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ubboyhalohalo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>bboyhalohalo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(11/4/01 7:27:42 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://designfront.8m.com/halologo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Question about styles/inking:)</span><hr size=1> whoo.. i dunno bout all the methods of preparation.. u can use ANY type of pen as long as your lines show you what u want them to... yknow?? that's MUCH too big a question for me to answer... each person has their own way..<br>
<br>
Different Anime/Manga styles??? most comics fall into one of two categories -- &quot;shonen&quot; - boys comics and &quot;shoujo&quot; - girls comics...<br>
<br>
shonen is your action stuph... shojo is romance .. but that's oversimplifying...<br>
<br>
shonen is basically plot oriented comics... lots more &quot;stuff&quot; happening.. people going from point A to point B..<br>
<br>
shojo is more cerebral or esoteric... more inner monologue and exploration of feelings..<br>
<br>
I think styles are better broken down into styles of storytelling, since there are actually many, many styles of drawing anime and manga<br>
<br>
<br>
haha if u can't see the differences between &quot;Marvel&quot; type comics and japanese comics.. that's a bad start already <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  but... if u notice, american style is much more detailed (usually) and people are drawn with prominent features to suggest their personality.. wheras in manga, people can look the same or be undetailed yet their dialogue or actions identify them... also their hair... this is because japanese comics are printed on cheap, recycled paper and bold, unique hairstyles help identify characters on the crappy paper... &gt;_&lt; i don't wanna do a history lesson but looking at ukiyo-e art from old japan can help explain some of the reasons behind the current styles of popular japanese illustrations...<br>
<br>
Wacom tablet is worth it if you PRACTICE!! it takes time to master the pressure sensitivity and such... but i think its a powerful tool...<br>
<br>
<br>
books??? just get a classical drawing technique book (anatomy and such) and adapt these to anime style... i don't think using a &quot;How-to-draw&quot; book will help as much and also may mess up your stylistic devlopment.. the best help  can come from comics!! get lots of em and in varying styles.. study inking technique and camera angles and everything.. train your eye..<br>
<br>
hope this helps.... &gt;_&lt; whoo lotsa typing...<br>
<br>
